, we find that for sufficiently large values of the GUP parameter\nand temperature, we obtain mass-radius relations that are completely removed\nfrom the ideal case, as high-mass deviations due to GUP and low-mass deviations\ndue to temperature are no longer mutually exclusive.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Oct 2022 14:22:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Oct 2022 14:07:22 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 27 Apr 2023 09:29:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-28"}
